WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.358 --> 00:00:11.048
[Boyd] Previously onFrom...

2
00:00:11.185 --> 00:00:12.225
[Sara] I hear their voices.

3
00:00:12.360 --> 00:00:14.670
They said it was
the only way to go home.

4
00:00:14.797 --> 00:00:16.407
Sara. just tell me
what you did.

5
00:00:16.538 --> 00:00:18.318
[Sara]
I left the door open.

6
00:00:18.453 --> 00:00:19.583
[Weeping]

7
00:00:19.715 --> 00:00:21.455
Are you living in town
or Colony House?

8
00:00:21.586 --> 00:00:22.846
-Town.
-Julie.

9
00:00:22.979 --> 00:00:24.419
Colony House.

10
00:00:24.546 --> 00:00:25.546
Why are you doing this?

11
00:00:25.677 --> 00:00:26.767
[Fatima] What's wrong?

12
00:00:26.896 --> 00:00:29.986
I think maybe
I-I made a mistake.

13
00:00:30.117 --> 00:00:33.897
[Fatima] Julie. there are
no mistakes. just choices.

14
00:00:34.034 --> 00:00:35.824
and you chose what was right
for you. and that matters.

15
00:00:35.948 --> 00:00:37.598
Come on.
try it out!

16
00:00:37.733 --> 00:00:39.433
[Kenny] Every single one
of these pins

17
00:00:39.561 --> 00:00:40.911
is a different resident
who drove in

18
00:00:41.041 --> 00:00:42.481
from a different location.

19
00:00:42.607 --> 00:00:45.567
That is fucking impossible.

20
00:00:45.697 --> 00:00:49.567
I don't just sit around.
accepting the world as it is!

21
00:00:49.701 --> 00:00:51.701
-[Static hisses on radio]
-Someone is doing this.

22
00:00:51.834 --> 00:00:53.494
and I'm not gonna rest
until I figure out how!

23
00:00:53.618 --> 00:00:54.878
[Father] I wish you had
the luxury of grief.

24
00:00:55.011 --> 00:00:56.531
but you don't. Boyd.

25
00:00:56.665 --> 00:00:58.925
These people need you.

26
00:00:59.059 --> 00:01:01.799
You need to be the one
to lead these people home.

27
00:01:01.931 --> 00:01:04.151
'Cause if you don't?
She died for nothing.

28
00:01:04.281 --> 00:01:06.941
What are you doing here?
You promised you'd stay home.

29
00:01:07.067 --> 00:01:08.627
If I didn't show up.
they would have wondered why.

30
00:01:08.764 --> 00:01:10.374
-It'll be okay.
-Sara...

31
00:01:10.505 --> 00:01:11.975
I promise.

32
00:01:12.115 --> 00:01:13.855
Do you wanna help me bring
over the rest of the food?

33
00:01:13.986 --> 00:01:15.376
Yeah!

34
00:01:16.641 --> 00:01:20.041
[Jim]
I just feel so... broken.

35
00:01:20.167 --> 00:01:22.387
We're gonna figure it
out together.

36
00:01:22.517 --> 00:01:23.737
Don't worry.

37
00:01:23.866 --> 00:01:24.736
Whatcha got there?

38
00:01:24.867 --> 00:01:25.867
Sweet potatoes.

39
00:01:25.998 --> 00:01:27.388
Ooh!

40
00:01:27.522 --> 00:01:30.442
Nice family.

41
00:01:30.568 --> 00:01:34.528
[Gasping breaths]

42
00:01:43.581 --> 00:01:44.891
[Ethan] Sara!

43
00:01:45.017 --> 00:01:46.187
[Boyd] Hey.
Oh! Oh. no. no. no.

44
00:01:46.323 --> 00:01:47.803
Okay. grab her.
grab her arm. grab her arm!

45
00:01:47.933 --> 00:01:49.413
Hold on. hold on!

46
00:01:54.723 --> 00:01:58.473
[Goats bleating]

47
00:01:58.596 --> 00:02:01.636
Hey. Alma. Come on.

48
00:02:01.773 --> 00:02:05.693
There you go. Alma.
a fresh batch just for you.

49
00:02:05.821 --> 00:02:08.691
Hey!
Make sure you share this time.

50
00:02:08.824 --> 00:02:12.574
Nathan! Nathan!

51
00:02:12.697 --> 00:02:15.567
It's your sister!
Something happened at the diner.

52
00:02:15.700 --> 00:02:16.830
They're taking her
to the clinic.

53
00:02:24.709 --> 00:02:26.839
I really am feeling much better.

54
00:02:26.972 --> 00:02:29.632
I still think you should spend
the night for observation. okay?

55
00:02:29.758 --> 00:02:30.848
Do I have to?

56
00:02:30.976 --> 00:02:32.106
It's just.
with things like this.

57
00:02:32.239 --> 00:02:35.109
it's best not to
take any chances. you know?

58
00:02:35.242 --> 00:02:36.682
I can have someone
go get Nathan.

59
00:02:36.808 --> 00:02:38.588
He can stay with you.

60
00:02:38.723 --> 00:02:42.773
No. He worries.
If he comes by.

61
00:02:42.901 --> 00:02:46.561
could you...
just tell him I'm sleeping.

62
00:02:46.688 --> 00:02:47.728
Yeah. no problem.

63
00:02:47.863 --> 00:02:50.473
[Door opening. closing]

64
00:02:54.739 --> 00:02:55.869
I'll. uh--
I'll be right back. okay?

65
00:03:05.185 --> 00:03:08.095
Hey. How's she doing?

66
00:03:08.231 --> 00:03:10.021
I mean. fine.
given the circumstances.

67
00:03:10.146 --> 00:03:13.146
Has this happened before?

68
00:03:13.280 --> 00:03:15.720
Well. I mean.
not according to Sara.

69
00:03:15.847 --> 00:03:17.847
And unless there's an MRI
machine tucked around somewhere.

70
00:03:17.980 --> 00:03:19.720
there's no way to really
know what's going on.

71
00:03:19.851 --> 00:03:21.421
-Yeah.
-I'm. uh...

72
00:03:21.549 --> 00:03:23.679
I'm gonna keep her overnight
and see if anything changes.

73
00:03:23.812 --> 00:03:26.032
Okay. You sure you're ready
for that?

74
00:03:26.162 --> 00:03:28.082
Look. I don't know
how that door got open.

75
00:03:28.208 --> 00:03:29.988
but I'm not gonna
let those things

76
00:03:30.122 --> 00:03:31.992
take this place
away from me.

77
00:03:32.124 --> 00:03:33.874
They've already taken
too much already.

78
00:03:33.996 --> 00:03:37.126
Yeah. They sure have.

79
00:03:37.260 --> 00:03:39.780
Hey. can I ask
you a question?

80
00:03:39.915 --> 00:03:43.785
These seizures - first.
the Matthews kid. now Sara.

81
00:03:43.919 --> 00:03:45.139
You think it's possible

82
00:03:45.268 --> 00:03:47.228
to have a physical
reaction to this place?

83
00:03:47.357 --> 00:03:50.187
Maybe something you
might normally diagnose

84
00:03:50.317 --> 00:03:52.057
as one thing on the outside.
but here it's--

85
00:03:52.188 --> 00:03:55.058
Look. Boyd. if you asked me
this six months ago.

86
00:03:55.191 --> 00:03:57.111
I would have said anything that
we've seen here was impossible.

87
00:03:57.237 --> 00:03:59.757
But the truth is. I...

88
00:03:59.891 --> 00:04:03.591
Okay. how long has
this been going on for?

89
00:04:05.897 --> 00:04:08.027
Long enough that it's got me
asking stupid questions.

90
00:04:08.160 --> 00:04:09.990
-Boyd...
-I'm fine.

91
00:04:10.119 --> 00:04:12.819
Come by tomorrow.
I want to take a look at it.

92
00:04:12.948 --> 00:04:14.598
No need.
I already know what it is.

93
00:04:17.039 --> 00:04:18.999
Nathan's here.

94
00:04:19.128 --> 00:04:20.518
[Sighing]
She doesn't want to see him.

95
00:04:22.827 --> 00:04:23.957
Yeah. I don't-- I don't know.

96
00:04:25.874 --> 00:04:28.014
Um. okay.
Go take care of your patient.

97
00:04:28.137 --> 00:04:29.827
I got this. okay?

98
00:04:29.965 --> 00:04:32.915
And I'm good.

99
00:04:33.055 --> 00:04:35.185
Whoa. whoa. whoa! Whoa!

100
00:04:35.318 --> 00:04:36.708
Is she okay?

101
00:04:36.841 --> 00:04:38.501
She's fine.
She's sleeping.

102
00:04:40.062 --> 00:04:42.152
I wanna see her.

103
00:04:42.282 --> 00:04:44.202
And you will. tomorrow.

104
00:04:44.327 --> 00:04:45.847
Kristi's gonna sit
with her tonight

105
00:04:45.981 --> 00:04:47.031
and make sure
everything is okay.

106
00:04:47.156 --> 00:04:48.766
No. no. I-I need
to see her now. please.

107
00:04:48.897 --> 00:04:50.457
You will. Hey. hey.

108
00:04:50.594 --> 00:04:52.904
Is there anything else going on
that we should know about?

109
00:04:53.031 --> 00:04:56.731
Anything that might help Kristi
figure out what's wrong?

110
00:04:56.861 --> 00:04:58.861
No. I'm just worried.
that's all.

111
00:04:58.994 --> 00:05:01.084
She's my little sister.

112
00:05:01.213 --> 00:05:05.783
Right. Look.

113
00:05:05.914 --> 00:05:09.794
this is Kristi's first
night back since... right?

114
00:05:09.918 --> 00:05:11.348
We don't want
to be going in there

115
00:05:11.485 --> 00:05:14.705
and making tonight more
stressful than it already is.

116
00:05:14.836 --> 00:05:16.786
Sara's in good hands.
Okay?

117
00:05:16.925 --> 00:05:19.135
Go home.
Get some sleep.

118
00:05:19.275 --> 00:05:20.795
You'll see her in the morning.

119
00:05:20.929 --> 00:05:22.189
Yeah.

120
00:05:22.322 --> 00:05:23.802
Okay?

121
00:05:40.035 --> 00:05:44.125
Is Sara gonna be okay?

122
00:05:44.256 --> 00:05:46.166
Well. yeah.
she's down at the clinic.

123
00:05:46.302 --> 00:05:47.742
They're gonna take
good care of her. Don't worry.

124
00:05:47.869 --> 00:05:49.349
You remember Kristi?

125
00:05:49.479 --> 00:05:52.399
The nice lady
who took care of your leg?

126
00:05:52.526 --> 00:05:55.696
She's gonna patch up Sara
the same way she patched you up.

127
00:05:55.833 --> 00:05:59.013
In the meantime.

128
00:05:59.141 --> 00:06:01.621
we are gonna
play a little game.

129
00:06:01.752 --> 00:06:04.842
For you.

130
00:06:04.973 --> 00:06:06.803
Well. we said we're gonna
figure it out. right?

131
00:06:06.931 --> 00:06:09.021
Let's figure it out.
Follow me.

132
00:06:10.805 --> 00:06:11.975
[Exhales]

133
00:06:17.115 --> 00:06:18.285
We're gonna do some
problem-solving.

134
00:06:18.421 --> 00:06:20.031
and the way
you problem solve

135
00:06:20.162 --> 00:06:21.822
is by asking questions.

136
00:06:21.946 --> 00:06:25.036
You ask every question
that might apply.

137
00:06:25.167 --> 00:06:27.297
no matter how crazy.
no matter how unlikely.

138
00:06:27.430 --> 00:06:30.040
You put it up on a board.
you get it out in front of you

139
00:06:30.172 --> 00:06:31.962
so that you can identify
everything you know

140
00:06:32.087 --> 00:06:34.087
and everything you don't.

141
00:06:34.219 --> 00:06:37.009
It'll be like telling
a story.

142
00:06:37.135 --> 00:06:40.745
Right. buddy?
Question number one.

143
00:06:42.967 --> 00:06:44.877
[Ethan] Dad!

144
00:06:45.013 --> 00:06:47.673
What? You never wanted
to write on a wall?

145
00:06:57.242 --> 00:07:01.162
There.
That's where we begin.

146
00:07:01.290 --> 00:07:11.210
♪

147
00:07:16.566 --> 00:07:21.216
["Que Sera. Sera [Whatever Will
Be. Will be]" plays]

148
00:07:21.353 --> 00:07:26.493
♪

149
00:07:26.620 --> 00:07:31.320
♪ When I was
just a little boy♪

150
00:07:31.451 --> 00:07:34.021
♪ I asked my father♪

151
00:07:34.149 --> 00:07:36.109
♪ "What will I be?"♪

152
00:07:37.326 --> 00:07:40.066
♪ "Will I be handsome?"♪

153
00:07:40.198 --> 00:07:42.368
♪ "Will I be rich?"♪

154
00:07:42.505 --> 00:07:45.675
♪ Here's what he said to me♪

155
00:07:46.814 --> 00:07:50.084
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

156
00:07:50.208 --> 00:07:53.688
♪ "Whatever will be. will be"♪

157
00:07:56.432 --> 00:07:59.962
♪ "The future's
Not ours to see"♪

158
00:08:00.088 --> 00:08:03.128
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

159
00:08:05.006 --> 00:08:07.696
♪ "What will be. will be"♪

160
00:08:17.279 --> 00:08:22.069
♪ Now
I have children of my own♪

161
00:08:22.197 --> 00:08:24.327
♪ They ask their father♪

162
00:08:24.460 --> 00:08:26.810
♪ "What will I be?♪

163
00:08:28.159 --> 00:08:30.469
"Will I be pretty?"♪

164
00:08:30.597 --> 00:08:33.077
♪ "Will I be rich?"♪

165
00:08:33.208 --> 00:08:35.298
♪ I tell them tenderly♪

166
00:08:38.213 --> 00:08:40.433
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

167
00:08:40.563 --> 00:08:45.533
♪ "Whatever will be. will be"♪

168
00:08:45.655 --> 00:08:50.225
♪ "The future's
Not ours to see"♪

169
00:08:50.355 --> 00:08:52.785
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

170
00:08:55.535 --> 00:08:58.095
♪ "What will be. will be"♪

171
00:09:00.365 --> 00:09:02.535
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

172
00:09:19.297 --> 00:09:24.037
[Crickets chirping]

173
00:09:41.189 --> 00:09:45.189
[Gasping breaths]

174
00:09:47.151 --> 00:09:48.071
Hey.

175
00:09:50.198 --> 00:09:53.108
I can't sleep.

176
00:09:53.244 --> 00:09:56.944
Uh. yeah. me neither.
I thought you'd like some tea?

177
00:09:57.074 --> 00:09:58.824
Do you want some?

178
00:10:01.035 --> 00:10:01.985
Sure.

179
00:10:09.565 --> 00:10:12.215
You and Kenny make
a really cute couple.

180
00:10:12.350 --> 00:10:14.400
Oh. uh. no.
we're just--

181
00:10:14.526 --> 00:10:15.876
we're just friends.

182
00:10:16.006 --> 00:10:17.566
Why?

183
00:10:17.704 --> 00:10:21.014
He's really sweet.
and he loves you.

184
00:10:21.142 --> 00:10:23.492
It's complicated.

185
00:10:23.623 --> 00:10:25.283
How?

186
00:10:25.407 --> 00:10:28.317
Well. 'cause I...
[Sighing]

187
00:10:28.453 --> 00:10:31.463
...have somebody at home.

188
00:10:31.587 --> 00:10:35.417
At least I think she's...
still... waiting.

189
00:10:37.245 --> 00:10:38.415
What's her name?

190
00:10:40.030 --> 00:10:42.210
Mariel.

191
00:10:42.337 --> 00:10:45.247
-Were you married?
-Engaged.

192
00:10:45.383 --> 00:10:49.523
I wonder sometimes.
actually all the time. uh.

193
00:10:49.649 --> 00:10:54.179
what it must be like for her.
thinking I. uh. abandoned her.

194
00:10:54.305 --> 00:10:57.085
Um. how about you?

195
00:10:57.221 --> 00:10:59.531
Do you have
anybody back at home?

196
00:10:59.659 --> 00:11:01.489
No.

197
00:11:01.617 --> 00:11:04.007
I... I was with someone.

198
00:11:04.141 --> 00:11:08.321
but he wasn't...

199
00:11:08.450 --> 00:11:13.110
It's better that
he's not around anymore.

200
00:11:13.237 --> 00:11:16.547
It's just me and Nathan now.

201
00:11:16.676 --> 00:11:20.586
He's all
I've got in the world.

202
00:11:20.723 --> 00:11:24.293
Before we got
stuck here. I. um...

203
00:11:24.422 --> 00:11:28.382
Things weren't
really very good for me.

204
00:11:28.513 --> 00:11:31.043
Nathan was
the one who saved me.

205
00:11:33.301 --> 00:11:35.041
Can I ask you something?

206
00:11:35.172 --> 00:11:37.612
Yeah. Sure.

207
00:11:37.740 --> 00:11:41.400
If there was
something you could do.

208
00:11:41.526 --> 00:11:46.176
something that would
let you see Mariel again...

209
00:11:47.707 --> 00:11:51.447
something that would let
everyone here go home.

210
00:11:51.580 --> 00:11:55.020
even if it was something bad.

211
00:11:55.149 --> 00:11:56.589
would you do it?

212
00:11:57.325 --> 00:11:59.755
Wait.
what are you talking about?

213
00:11:59.893 --> 00:12:04.643
I wonder sometimes...
about this place.

214
00:12:04.767 --> 00:12:08.077
what it means...

215
00:12:08.205 --> 00:12:10.115
why we're here.

216
00:12:11.643 --> 00:12:15.263
If someone came up to you
right now and said.

217
00:12:15.386 --> 00:12:18.126
"Do this one bad thing

218
00:12:18.259 --> 00:12:22.089
and everyone
gets to go home."

219
00:12:22.219 --> 00:12:24.219
would you do it?

220
00:12:24.352 --> 00:12:27.752
Well. we're...

221
00:12:27.877 --> 00:12:30.357
we're speaking
hypothetically. right?

222
00:12:30.488 --> 00:12:31.358
Yeah.

223
00:12:31.489 --> 00:12:32.359
Okay.

224
00:12:32.490 --> 00:12:33.580
Of course.

225
00:12:33.709 --> 00:12:35.229
[Chuckles]
Okay.

226
00:12:35.363 --> 00:12:36.493
Uh...

227
00:12:39.193 --> 00:12:42.673
I mean...

228
00:12:42.805 --> 00:12:45.235
Yeah. I'd. um...

229
00:12:45.373 --> 00:12:48.253
I'd do anything
to see her again and...

230
00:12:48.376 --> 00:12:49.766
And hey. I mean.

231
00:12:49.899 --> 00:12:51.729
if that meant everybody else
got to go home too.

232
00:12:51.858 --> 00:12:54.688
then. I think
that's a lot of good

233
00:12:54.817 --> 00:12:58.037
for one bad thing.

234
00:13:00.780 --> 00:13:02.000
Yeah.

235
00:13:10.354 --> 00:13:11.274
Hmm.

236
00:13:11.399 --> 00:13:13.619
[Exhales]

237
00:13:13.749 --> 00:13:15.229
Tell me you
figured it out.

238
00:13:15.359 --> 00:13:17.319
Oh. I-I did.

239
00:13:17.448 --> 00:13:19.578
And the answer is 12.

240
00:13:19.711 --> 00:13:22.761
[Chuckles]
Okay.

241
00:13:22.889 --> 00:13:25.539
All right.
let's go over this again.

242
00:13:28.546 --> 00:13:32.456
Everyone enters from different
parts of the country.

243
00:13:32.594 --> 00:13:34.904
on different roads.
in different places.

244
00:13:35.031 --> 00:13:37.251
and they all. presumably.
see the same tree.

245
00:13:37.381 --> 00:13:38.731
same crows.

246
00:13:38.861 --> 00:13:40.471
Jim. Jim...

247
00:13:40.602 --> 00:13:44.652
everyone here has asked the same
question over and over again.

248
00:13:44.780 --> 00:13:47.610
How does writing
them on the wall

249
00:13:47.739 --> 00:13:49.179
going to make
any difference?

250
00:13:49.306 --> 00:13:51.566
Because...

251
00:13:51.700 --> 00:13:54.090
There are plenty of things in
the world that don't make sense.

252
00:13:54.224 --> 00:13:55.404
Yeah.

253
00:13:55.530 --> 00:13:57.580
Something here
is missing.

254
00:13:58.750 --> 00:14:01.190
We just can't see it yet.

255
00:14:01.318 --> 00:14:02.448
But we will.

256
00:14:02.580 --> 00:14:05.500
Well. there's a question
we haven't asked.

257
00:14:17.769 --> 00:14:19.289
No.

258
00:14:19.423 --> 00:14:22.383
Why not?

259
00:14:23.079 --> 00:14:26.209
Because it's crazy.
[Sighing]

260
00:14:30.478 --> 00:14:32.348
I don't want
to know the answer.

261
00:14:38.834 --> 00:14:41.274
You sure you're not hungry?
I was gonna make some oatmeal.

262
00:14:41.402 --> 00:14:42.792
I'm not really hungry.

263
00:14:42.925 --> 00:14:44.795
Thank you
for last night. though.

264
00:14:44.927 --> 00:14:47.227
It's been a long time
since I've had a girls' night.

265
00:14:47.364 --> 00:14:48.804
Yeah. uh. me too.

266
00:14:48.931 --> 00:14:51.631
I mean. hey. no need to wait
for a medical emergency

267
00:14:51.760 --> 00:14:54.460
if you ever wanna
do it again.

268
00:14:55.807 --> 00:14:57.457
Oh. your brother's back.

269
00:14:57.592 --> 00:15:00.512
Uh. he's very persistent.

270
00:15:00.638 --> 00:15:03.338
Yeah. he is.

271
00:15:03.467 --> 00:15:04.897
Are you-- are you
sure you're okay?

272
00:15:05.034 --> 00:15:07.694
Yeah. yeah. it's fine.
He just-- he cares a lot.

273
00:15:07.819 --> 00:15:09.209
Yeah.

274
00:15:09.343 --> 00:15:10.393
I'll see you later.

275
00:15:12.824 --> 00:15:14.874
You're up bright
and early.

276
00:15:15.001 --> 00:15:16.351
Sara. we need
to talk.

277
00:15:16.480 --> 00:15:17.610
About what?

278
00:15:19.701 --> 00:15:21.831
I'm so sorry I worried you.
I didn't mean to.

279
00:15:21.964 --> 00:15:24.754
It's fine. I just need
to know what happened.

280
00:15:24.880 --> 00:15:26.530
I was just...

281
00:15:26.664 --> 00:15:29.324
I was standing
in the diner one minute

282
00:15:29.450 --> 00:15:30.710
and the next.
I was on the floor.

283
00:15:30.842 --> 00:15:32.802
I don't really remember
much other than that.

284
00:15:32.932 --> 00:15:34.722
Why are you suddenly acting
like everything's okay?

285
00:15:34.846 --> 00:15:35.666
I need to get
to the diner.

286
00:15:35.804 --> 00:15:37.284
Mrs. Liu is
gonna be worried.

287
00:15:37.414 --> 00:15:38.554
Sara!

288
00:15:38.676 --> 00:15:41.546
I'm okay. I promise.

289
00:15:41.679 --> 00:15:43.249
I love you so much.

290
00:15:52.864 --> 00:15:55.744
Knock. knock.
You awake in there?

291
00:15:55.867 --> 00:15:57.777
Yeah. come on in.

292
00:15:57.913 --> 00:16:00.353
Whatcha doing?

293
00:16:00.481 --> 00:16:01.571
I'm making a list.

294
00:16:01.699 --> 00:16:04.399
Of?

295
00:16:04.528 --> 00:16:05.878
All the people
that are probably

296
00:16:06.008 --> 00:16:07.528
wondering where
we are right now.

297
00:16:07.662 --> 00:16:09.012
Oh.

298
00:16:09.142 --> 00:16:10.882
I mean. it's gotta be
worse for them. right?

299
00:16:11.013 --> 00:16:13.843
Not knowing.

300
00:16:13.973 --> 00:16:15.453
Just...

301
00:16:18.760 --> 00:16:21.070
I made one too.

302
00:16:21.197 --> 00:16:24.587
Pretty sure everybody here
did at one time or another.

303
00:16:28.422 --> 00:16:30.382
Who's on yours?

304
00:16:31.686 --> 00:16:35.206
My grandparents
and my friends.

305
00:16:37.866 --> 00:16:39.256
Boyfriend?

306
00:16:39.389 --> 00:16:40.909
No.

307
00:16:41.043 --> 00:16:42.523
Girlfriend?

308
00:16:42.653 --> 00:16:46.833
No. there's
nobody like that.

309
00:16:46.962 --> 00:16:49.702
I guess that's a good thing
though. right?

310
00:16:49.834 --> 00:16:51.844
Just one less person sitting
around losing their minds.

311
00:16:51.967 --> 00:16:53.797
wondering where you are.

312
00:16:53.925 --> 00:16:56.705
[Exhales] Okay.
That's enough of that.

313
00:16:56.841 --> 00:16:59.541
We need some fun. stat.

314
00:16:59.670 --> 00:17:01.460
Get dressed and meet me
downstairs in five?

315
00:17:01.585 --> 00:17:02.795
Why?

316
00:17:02.934 --> 00:17:03.894
You'll see.

317
00:17:04.023 --> 00:17:06.723
[Sighs]

318
00:17:06.851 --> 00:17:10.511
[Metallic clanking]

319
00:17:12.596 --> 00:17:13.636
Hey.

320
00:17:13.771 --> 00:17:15.601
Hey.

321
00:17:15.730 --> 00:17:18.600
No more work
this morning.

322
00:17:18.733 --> 00:17:20.693
She's. uh.
making the list.

323
00:17:24.652 --> 00:17:26.832
I think it's time we
show her the Brundles.

324
00:17:30.179 --> 00:17:32.659
Just a fucking idiot.
That's special relativity.

325
00:17:32.790 --> 00:17:34.790
Uh... Klein.

326
00:17:34.923 --> 00:17:37.803
Hardy's.
Klein. Hardy's.

327
00:17:41.016 --> 00:17:42.536
Einstein-Podolsky-Rosen.

328
00:17:42.670 --> 00:17:44.370
[Trudy] Where are you
going with that?

329
00:17:46.674 --> 00:17:48.374
Sorry?

330
00:17:48.502 --> 00:17:50.722
Is that a radio?

331
00:17:50.852 --> 00:17:54.642
Uh... yeah.
Sort of.

332
00:17:54.769 --> 00:17:57.599
Why are you carrying it around?

333
00:17:58.947 --> 00:18:02.427
[Sighing]
Because it helps me think.

334
00:18:02.559 --> 00:18:03.999
I'm sorry. I--

335
00:18:04.126 --> 00:18:05.736
You're even cuter
when you're awake.

336
00:18:05.867 --> 00:18:07.517
Excuse me?

337
00:18:07.651 --> 00:18:09.651
I watched you when
you were sleeping.

338
00:18:09.784 --> 00:18:10.964
I'm Trudy.

339
00:18:11.090 --> 00:18:13.880
Okay.

340
00:18:14.005 --> 00:18:15.825
Too bad you chose the town.

341
00:18:18.749 --> 00:18:22.319
I would've rode you
like an alabaster dragon.

342
00:18:24.494 --> 00:18:25.584
Bye!

343
00:18:40.597 --> 00:18:41.767
[Door opening]

344
00:18:41.903 --> 00:18:43.513
Morning. Sheriff.

345
00:18:43.644 --> 00:18:46.914
I stopped by the diner. let my
mom know that Sara was okay.

346
00:18:47.038 --> 00:18:48.868
and she made those
bread things that you like.

347
00:18:48.997 --> 00:18:50.647
so I picked up
a couple of those.

348
00:18:52.000 --> 00:18:54.480
Uh. Sheriff?

349
00:18:58.180 --> 00:19:00.790
I'm gonna need you to
hold down the fort for a bit.

350
00:19:00.922 --> 00:19:03.752
Is everything okay?

351
00:19:03.881 --> 00:19:06.931
Everything's fine.

352
00:19:07.058 --> 00:19:08.888
I'm gonna visit my wife.

353
00:19:09.017 --> 00:19:10.367
It's been a while.

354
00:19:14.718 --> 00:19:15.808
Okay?

355
00:19:15.937 --> 00:19:17.807
Yeah. sure.

356
00:19:22.683 --> 00:19:25.693
[Door opening. closing]

357
00:19:25.816 --> 00:19:26.986
[Jade] What the hell?

358
00:19:27.122 --> 00:19:30.652
You guys built a bar
in this fucking place?

359
00:19:30.778 --> 00:19:31.778
Yeah.
You end up in a place like this.

360
00:19:31.909 --> 00:19:34.169
you ask yourself.
what do the people need?

361
00:19:34.303 --> 00:19:37.613
Turns out it's not a fucking gas
station. so I figured...

362
00:19:37.741 --> 00:19:41.481
[Chattering]

363
00:19:41.615 --> 00:19:42.745
Hey. you okay?

364
00:19:42.877 --> 00:19:44.567
What?

365
00:19:44.705 --> 00:19:46.575
Are... you... okay?

366
00:19:46.707 --> 00:19:48.837
No. no. I'm not... okay.

367
00:19:50.058 --> 00:19:52.578
Are you okay?

368
00:19:52.713 --> 00:19:54.633
Great.
Here. drink this.

369
00:19:54.758 --> 00:19:55.928
It'll help you feel better.

370
00:19:56.064 --> 00:19:57.984
What the fuck?
How are you--

371
00:19:58.109 --> 00:20:00.679
why are you all
just sitting here?

372
00:20:00.808 --> 00:20:02.898
[Gags]

373
00:20:03.027 --> 00:20:05.727
Holy fuck!
What is this shit?

374
00:20:05.856 --> 00:20:08.816
Just consider it your
poor man's potato vodka.

375
00:20:08.946 --> 00:20:12.466
[Groans]

376
00:20:12.602 --> 00:20:14.432
[Groans]

377
00:20:17.128 --> 00:20:19.038
You're one of the guys
from the two cars. huh?

378
00:20:19.174 --> 00:20:22.004
[Groans]

379
00:20:22.133 --> 00:20:25.143
Your. uh. friend. uh--
friend got. uh...

380
00:20:25.267 --> 00:20:27.837
Yeah. Yeah.

381
00:20:27.965 --> 00:20:31.185
Look. if it's
any consolation. it--

382
00:20:31.317 --> 00:20:33.487
it gets easier. man.
it really does.

383
00:20:33.623 --> 00:20:34.803
[Scoffs]

384
00:20:34.929 --> 00:20:37.889
Gets easier.
that's rich.

385
00:20:38.019 --> 00:20:39.719
That is fucking rich.

386
00:20:42.371 --> 00:20:46.161
You know. you guys are--
you're like rats in a maze.

387
00:20:46.288 --> 00:20:50.598
sitting there. contentedly...

388
00:20:50.727 --> 00:20:52.597
nibbling on your cheese.

389
00:20:56.298 --> 00:20:58.608
This is a paradox.

390
00:20:59.780 --> 00:21:02.000
That's the problem.

391
00:21:02.130 --> 00:21:05.310
[Breathes deeply]

392
00:21:05.438 --> 00:21:08.048
The immediate question is.
how do we get home. right?

393
00:21:08.179 --> 00:21:10.969
How do we get out?
How do we get out of here?

394
00:21:13.141 --> 00:21:15.621
'Cause unless we
know where "here" is.

395
00:21:15.752 --> 00:21:17.062
we can't get outta here.

396
00:21:17.188 --> 00:21:20.058
It's like-- it's like... this.
it's like. uh.

397
00:21:20.191 --> 00:21:22.111
hitting a bull's-eye with
your eyes closed. right?

398
00:21:22.237 --> 00:21:23.717
You're just throwing 'em blind!

399
00:21:23.847 --> 00:21:26.107
You don't even fucking know
where the fucking target is!

400
00:21:26.241 --> 00:21:27.851
Maybe it's over here!
I don't know!

401
00:21:27.982 --> 00:21:29.292
Maybe it just. like.
went that way!

402
00:21:29.418 --> 00:21:32.598
-Whoa. whoa. whoa! Come on!
-[Jade] Throwing it!

403
00:21:32.726 --> 00:21:33.986
Settle down.

404
00:21:34.118 --> 00:21:36.768
Eventually. you just
get tired. you give up.

405
00:21:36.904 --> 00:21:38.994
You accept that
you can't just get out.

406
00:21:39.123 --> 00:21:40.083
'cause you have
no fucking idea

407
00:21:40.211 --> 00:21:41.691
where you're
trying to get out of.

408
00:21:41.822 --> 00:21:45.132
So. you sit around drinking
your acidic potato piss water

409
00:21:45.260 --> 00:21:46.910
that you call vodka.

410
00:21:47.044 --> 00:21:48.134
Yeah.

411
00:21:48.263 --> 00:21:50.793
So. let me guess.

412
00:21:50.918 --> 00:21:52.958
you're gonna be the guy
who figures it all out.

413
00:21:53.094 --> 00:21:55.054
You're goddamn right I am.

414
00:21:55.183 --> 00:21:57.663
People like me.
we design the maze.

415
00:21:57.794 --> 00:22:00.844
we place the cheese.

416
00:22:00.971 --> 00:22:03.191
I don't know what
you did before you got here.

417
00:22:03.322 --> 00:22:05.932
but I just sold a company
for an obscene amount of money

418
00:22:06.063 --> 00:22:08.153
based on a quantum
computing algorithm

419
00:22:08.283 --> 00:22:10.723
with the potential to...

420
00:22:10.851 --> 00:22:14.121
[Sighs]
I'm not supposed to be here.

421
00:22:14.245 --> 00:22:17.115
I'm supposed to be
celebrating right now at...

422
00:22:19.468 --> 00:22:21.168
Look. the point is
we can't get out of here

423
00:22:21.296 --> 00:22:23.426
unless we know where "here" is.

424
00:22:23.559 --> 00:22:26.169
Right? To solve the paradox. you
gotta understand the paradox.

425
00:22:26.301 --> 00:22:28.041
You gotta identify it.
You gotta frame it.

426
00:22:28.172 --> 00:22:31.002
-Schrodinger's cat.
-What?

427
00:22:31.132 --> 00:22:33.482
Schrodinger's cat.
that-- that's the paradox.

428
00:22:33.613 --> 00:22:36.313
You put the cat in the box
and you close the box.

429
00:22:36.442 --> 00:22:37.832
As long as you never
open it again...

430
00:22:37.965 --> 00:22:40.315
The cat is theoretically alive
and dead at the same time.

431
00:22:40.446 --> 00:22:43.226
I know what
Schrodinger's cat is.

432
00:22:43.362 --> 00:22:46.282
Okay. so.
we're the cat.

433
00:22:46.408 --> 00:22:50.188
This place here
is the box. right?

434
00:22:50.325 --> 00:22:55.155
So. all those people
we left behind back home?

435
00:22:55.286 --> 00:22:56.896
Well. they're all
sitting around wondering

436
00:22:57.027 --> 00:22:59.027
if we're alive or dead.

437
00:22:59.160 --> 00:23:02.080
So. to them. we're both
things at the same time.

438
00:23:05.296 --> 00:23:07.996
I taught
Intro to Philosophy at USC.

439
00:23:08.125 --> 00:23:10.255
Hmm.

440
00:23:10.389 --> 00:23:13.169
Look. uh. I don't know
a fuckin' thing about computers.

441
00:23:13.304 --> 00:23:15.054
I'll be the first
to admit that.

442
00:23:15.176 --> 00:23:17.306
But that. uh--
that radio you brought in.

443
00:23:17.439 --> 00:23:19.959
well. if you're
so goddamn smart.

444
00:23:20.094 --> 00:23:22.104
why don't you figure out how
to get it broadcasting. huh?

445
00:23:22.226 --> 00:23:24.316
And I'll tell you what.

446
00:23:24.446 --> 00:23:29.096
if the cat
turns on the radio.

447
00:23:29.233 --> 00:23:31.983
you can be goddamn sure that
the people outside the box

448
00:23:32.106 --> 00:23:34.626
are at least gonna
know it's still alive.

449
00:23:37.981 --> 00:23:40.071
Huh.

450
00:23:42.725 --> 00:23:48.725
♪

451
00:24:01.352 --> 00:24:03.272
Are you sure
this doesn't hurt?

452
00:24:03.398 --> 00:24:05.788
It's just a little sore.

453
00:24:07.184 --> 00:24:08.884
Hm.

454
00:24:09.012 --> 00:24:09.972
What's wrong?

455
00:24:10.100 --> 00:24:11.800
Nothing.
It's...

456
00:24:15.366 --> 00:24:17.276
[Sighing] It's just...

457
00:24:17.412 --> 00:24:20.202
It's just healing
so fast.

458
00:24:20.328 --> 00:24:22.198
Is that bad?

459
00:24:22.330 --> 00:24:24.850
No. No.

460
00:24:24.985 --> 00:24:27.375
Um. actually.
it's very good.

461
00:24:27.509 --> 00:24:30.249
I think this place is special.

462
00:24:30.381 --> 00:24:33.251
I know it tries
to hurt people.

463
00:24:33.384 --> 00:24:36.434
but maybe it tries
to help people too.

464
00:24:36.562 --> 00:24:40.172
Maybe that can be one of
the questions on the wall.

465
00:24:40.304 --> 00:24:41.924
What would that be?

466
00:24:42.045 --> 00:24:45.395
Is there anyone
trying to help?

467
00:24:45.527 --> 00:24:48.097
[Chuckles]

468
00:24:48.225 --> 00:24:50.395
[Kissing noise]
That's a great question.

469
00:24:50.532 --> 00:24:52.492
[Jim] Ethan!
You have a visitor!

470
00:24:52.621 --> 00:24:56.021
Oh.
Let's see who that is.

471
00:24:58.366 --> 00:24:59.926
[Ethan] Sara!

472
00:25:00.063 --> 00:25:01.853
How's my
favorite customer?

473
00:25:01.978 --> 00:25:03.888
We drew on the walls.

474
00:25:04.024 --> 00:25:06.424
I see that.

475
00:25:06.548 --> 00:25:08.938
We never draw on
the walls at home.

476
00:25:09.072 --> 00:25:11.032
[Chuckles]

477
00:25:11.161 --> 00:25:12.991
How are you feeling?

478
00:25:13.120 --> 00:25:14.340
Much better. thank you.

479
00:25:14.469 --> 00:25:16.339
Good. Uh. did Kristi
figure out what happened?

480
00:25:16.471 --> 00:25:19.301
Not yet. It's...

481
00:25:19.430 --> 00:25:21.170
It's just one of
those things. I guess.

482
00:25:21.302 --> 00:25:22.482
[Tabitha] Yeah.

483
00:25:22.608 --> 00:25:23.958
[Ethan] There's
a playground outside.

484
00:25:24.087 --> 00:25:25.957
Wanna see?

485
00:25:26.089 --> 00:25:27.919
Hey. honey. Sara just
came out of the hospital.

486
00:25:28.048 --> 00:25:29.218
Sure.

487
00:25:29.353 --> 00:25:30.273
Okay.

488
00:25:30.398 --> 00:25:31.918
Yeah.

489
00:25:32.052 --> 00:25:34.012
[Stammers]
It's okay. really. Yeah.

490
00:25:34.141 --> 00:25:35.321
-Come on!
-Be careful.

491
00:25:42.541 --> 00:25:44.541
This one's my favorite.

492
00:25:57.251 --> 00:26:07.221
♪

493
00:26:12.005 --> 00:26:14.215
Hello?

494
00:26:18.141 --> 00:26:19.581
Father Khatri?

495
00:26:22.276 --> 00:26:27.496
♪

496
00:26:27.629 --> 00:26:30.589
[Laughing]

497
00:26:30.719 --> 00:26:33.029
[Ellis]
Welcome to the Brundles!

498
00:26:33.156 --> 00:26:34.196
[Laughing]

499
00:26:34.331 --> 00:26:36.941
Whoo!

500
00:26:37.073 --> 00:26:38.293
[Julie] Oh. God!

501
00:26:40.555 --> 00:26:42.465
Oh!
[Chuckling]

502
00:26:42.601 --> 00:26:44.171
[Sighing contentedly]

503
00:26:45.299 --> 00:26:47.259
See?
If you close your eyes

504
00:26:47.388 --> 00:26:48.908
and just listen.

505
00:26:49.042 --> 00:26:52.962
it's almost like being
anywhere else in the world.

506
00:26:53.089 --> 00:26:54.089
How do you do that?

507
00:26:55.178 --> 00:26:56.088
Do what?

508
00:26:57.528 --> 00:27:00.528
How do you act
like this place doesn't...

509
00:27:00.662 --> 00:27:02.492
You're always so positive.

510
00:27:03.796 --> 00:27:06.316
I guess it all just depends on
how you choose to look at it.

511
00:27:07.495 --> 00:27:09.315
What do you mean?

512
00:27:11.586 --> 00:27:15.586
Well. I didn't come to
the U.S. until I was 11.

513
00:27:15.721 --> 00:27:18.641
I grew up in
a small village in Iran

514
00:27:18.767 --> 00:27:21.247
with my parents
and two older brothers.

515
00:27:21.378 --> 00:27:26.168
My father. he was
a very outspoken cleric.

516
00:27:26.296 --> 00:27:29.646
which wasn't always the most
popular thing to be at the time.

517
00:27:31.258 --> 00:27:33.478
One day. it was my birthday.

518
00:27:33.608 --> 00:27:38.128
Actually. we were getting
ready to go see my uncle.

519
00:27:38.265 --> 00:27:42.305
These men showed up.
They were angry. shouting.

520
00:27:42.443 --> 00:27:45.103
I remember my mother
told me to hide.

521
00:27:46.316 --> 00:27:50.446
But I was so confused
because we were just laughing.

522
00:27:50.581 --> 00:27:52.451
My father had told
this story about...

523
00:27:57.414 --> 00:27:59.684
He was a really
good storyteller.

524
00:27:59.808 --> 00:28:03.328
I think that's what made him
such an effective preacher.

525
00:28:03.464 --> 00:28:07.424
Anyway. I could tell
my mother was afraid.

526
00:28:07.555 --> 00:28:10.205
My brothers had run to the door
and now they were shouting too.

527
00:28:10.340 --> 00:28:14.170
and my mother just kept
saying "Hide. hide."

528
00:28:14.301 --> 00:28:17.431
But I just stood there.
I couldn't move.

529
00:28:17.565 --> 00:28:20.175
because it was all so strange.

530
00:28:20.307 --> 00:28:24.527
I mean. we were just laughing
so hard. you know?

531
00:28:24.659 --> 00:28:27.229
It was gonna be
the best birthday ever.

532
00:28:27.357 --> 00:28:29.397
The sun was so bright
coming in through the door

533
00:28:29.533 --> 00:28:32.103
that my father
became a silhouette

534
00:28:32.232 --> 00:28:34.712
when they dragged him outside.

535
00:28:39.718 --> 00:28:43.418
And then. there was this pop.

536
00:28:43.547 --> 00:28:46.547
like a firecracker.

537
00:28:46.681 --> 00:28:48.941
and the silhouette fell down.

538
00:28:51.207 --> 00:28:52.947
Oh. my God.

539
00:28:55.516 --> 00:28:58.736
The point is.

540
00:28:58.867 --> 00:29:01.517
there are always going to
be monsters in the world.

541
00:29:01.652 --> 00:29:03.522
It doesn't matter
where you are.

542
00:29:03.654 --> 00:29:05.704
But I promised myself

543
00:29:05.831 --> 00:29:08.701
I would never let them
scare the life out of me.

544
00:29:08.834 --> 00:29:11.494
-Oh. hey. hi.
-Hi!

545
00:29:12.446 --> 00:29:14.536
Ah. yeah. you just
look too dry. Come here!

546
00:29:14.665 --> 00:29:17.705
Oh. no. no. no!
No. no. no. no!

547
00:29:17.843 --> 00:29:20.153
[Ellis] Come on. Come on.
Come on. Yup. we're goin'!

548
00:29:20.280 --> 00:29:22.150
We're goin'! Hey!

549
00:29:22.282 --> 00:29:24.022
[Fatima]
Julie. come on!

550
00:29:24.153 --> 00:29:25.553
Come on!

551
00:29:25.676 --> 00:29:28.546
[Metal squeaking]

552
00:29:31.334 --> 00:29:32.384
That's the most like himself

553
00:29:32.509 --> 00:29:34.249
I've seen Ethan
since the accident.

554
00:29:34.381 --> 00:29:36.471
[Metal squeaking]

555
00:29:36.600 --> 00:29:38.600
How long have you lived here?

556
00:29:38.733 --> 00:29:41.303
Just a few months.

557
00:29:41.431 --> 00:29:43.431
Mom and Dad are trying to
figure out where we are

558
00:29:43.564 --> 00:29:45.224
so we can all go home.

559
00:29:45.348 --> 00:29:47.608
That's what
the Cromenockle would do.

560
00:29:47.742 --> 00:29:49.532
What's a Cromenockle?

561
00:29:49.657 --> 00:29:53.177
[Tabitha]
She's a sweet girl.

562
00:29:56.316 --> 00:29:58.136
Hey. honey.
Don't make her sit there.

563
00:29:58.274 --> 00:29:59.894
Those things are filthy.

564
00:30:00.015 --> 00:30:03.315
It's okay.
It's-- it's actually kinda fun.

565
00:30:03.453 --> 00:30:07.153
Sara said we can go see the
goats and chickens at the barn.

566
00:30:07.283 --> 00:30:08.813
Really?

567
00:30:08.937 --> 00:30:10.897
My brother. he tends to all
the animals for the town.

568
00:30:11.026 --> 00:30:12.636
I thought it might
be fun to show Ethan.

569
00:30:12.767 --> 00:30:14.637
It's just down the street.

570
00:30:14.769 --> 00:30:17.419
Do you want to go?
I'm gonna tell Dad we're going.

571
00:30:17.554 --> 00:30:19.514
[Sara]
I can take him.

572
00:30:19.643 --> 00:30:20.603
I don't want to
take you guys away

573
00:30:20.731 --> 00:30:22.431
from anything
that you're doing.

574
00:30:22.559 --> 00:30:24.649
We're not doing anything.
Hey. Jim.

575
00:30:24.779 --> 00:30:26.429
I'll be right back.

576
00:30:26.563 --> 00:30:28.353
Okay.

577
00:30:32.613 --> 00:30:37.403
[Birds chirping]

578
00:30:41.274 --> 00:30:43.154
Hey. babe.

579
00:30:44.712 --> 00:30:47.322
It's been a while.

580
00:30:47.454 --> 00:30:50.814
Things have been...

581
00:30:50.936 --> 00:30:54.196
they've been a little
crazy past few days.

582
00:30:54.330 --> 00:30:57.510
Those. uh. things...

583
00:30:57.638 --> 00:31:00.858
they. uh...

584
00:31:00.989 --> 00:31:04.729
they got into the house
where the little girl lived.

585
00:31:04.863 --> 00:31:07.473
got into the clinic.

586
00:31:08.736 --> 00:31:11.256
You know. we were doing
pretty good for a while there.

587
00:31:11.391 --> 00:31:12.871
keeping everything together.

588
00:31:13.001 --> 00:31:14.661
It was almost
starting to feel like...

589
00:31:21.488 --> 00:31:22.448
[Clears throat]

590
00:31:26.362 --> 00:31:28.892
Uh...

591
00:31:29.017 --> 00:31:33.407
I started getting tremors
in my hand a few weeks back.

592
00:31:33.543 --> 00:31:36.333
same way it started with my Dad.

593
00:31:36.459 --> 00:31:39.249
which means the clock
is officially ticking.

594
00:31:40.507 --> 00:31:44.417
But. see. uh...

595
00:31:44.554 --> 00:31:47.214
I have this crazy idea
that might actually work.

596
00:31:47.340 --> 00:31:49.470
and-and if it does.

597
00:31:49.603 --> 00:31:53.823
then I might be able to find
a way to get these people home.

598
00:31:53.955 --> 00:31:58.435
to get Ellis home.

599
00:31:58.568 --> 00:32:02.358
Of course if it doesn't.
if I'm wrong or if I fail.

600
00:32:02.485 --> 00:32:04.615
then. uh...

601
00:32:04.748 --> 00:32:06.748
then I'm leaving these people
in a worse-off position

602
00:32:06.881 --> 00:32:09.141
than they already are.

603
00:32:12.800 --> 00:32:16.590
You were always the one...
[Chuckles]

604
00:32:16.717 --> 00:32:18.717
You made all the hard calls.

605
00:32:18.849 --> 00:32:21.329
"Sometimes you got
to swing big. baby."

606
00:32:21.461 --> 00:32:23.681
[Laughs]
'Member that?

607
00:32:23.811 --> 00:32:25.601
[Laughs]

608
00:32:25.726 --> 00:32:28.246
God. you had...
[Laughs]

609
00:32:29.599 --> 00:32:31.599
[Laughs]

610
00:32:33.603 --> 00:32:36.613
[Stammers] I do this

611
00:32:36.737 --> 00:32:38.867
and that's about as big
a swing as I can take.

612
00:32:39.000 --> 00:32:41.740
And. um...

613
00:32:41.872 --> 00:32:44.142
And look. I know.
I know. I always said

614
00:32:44.266 --> 00:32:48.526
that I don't believe in signs
or any of that stuff. but...

615
00:32:51.056 --> 00:32:53.616
I could really use
one right now. okay?

616
00:32:55.930 --> 00:32:59.760
'Cause. babe.
I'm standing at the plate.

617
00:32:59.890 --> 00:33:02.280
and I'll swing if you
tell me to swing. I just...

618
00:33:07.072 --> 00:33:08.642
Babe. I just need
a little help here.

619
00:33:08.769 --> 00:33:10.249
Come on.

620
00:33:11.598 --> 00:33:13.468
I need a sign.

621
00:33:13.600 --> 00:33:15.470
[Birds chirping]

622
00:33:21.477 --> 00:33:23.307
Father Khatri?

623
00:33:25.742 --> 00:33:27.742
Nathan.

624
00:33:27.875 --> 00:33:30.395
Have you come up here much?

625
00:33:30.530 --> 00:33:32.580
No. not really.

626
00:33:32.706 --> 00:33:34.316
It's strange.
don't you think?

627
00:33:34.447 --> 00:33:37.797
A place like this...

628
00:33:37.928 --> 00:33:41.238
could exist in
a place like this?

629
00:33:43.760 --> 00:33:46.810
Um...

630
00:33:46.937 --> 00:33:50.897
I was wondering.
what are the rules?

631
00:33:51.029 --> 00:33:55.559
When it comes to confession.

632
00:33:55.685 --> 00:33:58.945
if I tell you something.

633
00:33:59.080 --> 00:34:00.690
does it stay between
the two of us?

634
00:34:00.821 --> 00:34:03.351
Anything you tell me
stays between us and God.

635
00:34:04.651 --> 00:34:06.521
What if it's bad?

636
00:34:08.698 --> 00:34:10.568
What if it's really bad?

637
00:34:12.876 --> 00:34:13.826
That one's name
is Alma.

638
00:34:13.964 --> 00:34:14.924
Hi. Alma.

639
00:34:15.053 --> 00:34:16.973
[Tabitha chuckles]

640
00:34:17.098 --> 00:34:18.798
Oh. this is so much fun.
Thank you.

641
00:34:18.926 --> 00:34:20.966
It's my pleasure.

642
00:34:21.102 --> 00:34:23.672
Really.
he's a little sweetheart.

643
00:34:25.628 --> 00:34:26.928
Yeah.

644
00:34:27.065 --> 00:34:29.325
You have
a really nice family.

645
00:34:29.458 --> 00:34:31.418
Hmm.

646
00:34:32.940 --> 00:34:35.510
It's okay to be sad.
you know?

647
00:34:37.771 --> 00:34:39.291
And it's okay
to be afraid.

648
00:34:42.993 --> 00:34:44.563
Yeah. it seems the one thing

649
00:34:44.691 --> 00:34:46.691
that everyone
in this town agrees on.

650
00:34:48.912 --> 00:34:50.872
Really. though.
you'd be surprised

651
00:34:51.001 --> 00:34:53.531
how quickly
all this becomes normal.

652
00:34:57.747 --> 00:35:01.487
I don't want this
to become normal.

653
00:35:01.621 --> 00:35:03.671
I just want
to go back home.

654
00:35:04.798 --> 00:35:05.798
Me too.

655
00:35:08.845 --> 00:35:10.715
At least we have
the talismans. though.

656
00:35:10.847 --> 00:35:12.547
Father Khatri
always talks about

657
00:35:12.675 --> 00:35:13.885
how much worse
it was for people.

658
00:35:14.024 --> 00:35:16.594
They'd just hide
in places after dark.

659
00:35:16.723 --> 00:35:19.553
hoping the monsters
wouldn't find them.

660
00:35:19.682 --> 00:35:21.122
Those hiding places
are all over town.

661
00:35:21.249 --> 00:35:23.819
It's really good
to know about them.

662
00:35:23.947 --> 00:35:26.467
just in case you ever
get stuck outside after dark.

663
00:35:26.602 --> 00:35:28.652
Yeah. I guess.

664
00:35:28.778 --> 00:35:30.908
There's one in the barn.
I can show you where it is.

665
00:35:31.041 --> 00:35:32.871
Really?

666
00:35:33.000 --> 00:35:35.130
Yeah. it's just...
It's right inside.

667
00:35:37.700 --> 00:35:38.830
Uh. yeah.

668
00:35:41.139 --> 00:35:44.489
Honey. uh. I'll be right back.
okay? Don't move.

669
00:35:44.620 --> 00:35:45.800
[Sara] This way.

670
00:35:56.241 --> 00:36:00.111
Nathan. you should've
come to me much sooner.

671
00:36:00.245 --> 00:36:02.595
I didn't--
Wait. wait.

672
00:36:02.725 --> 00:36:03.985
What's gonna happen to her?

673
00:36:04.118 --> 00:36:05.818
[Stammers] I don't want
her to go in the box.

674
00:36:05.946 --> 00:36:07.506
You gave your word.

675
00:36:07.643 --> 00:36:09.253
And I intend to keep it.

676
00:36:09.384 --> 00:36:11.734
But right now. we have to worry
about the people of the town.

677
00:36:11.865 --> 00:36:13.035
She'll be at the diner.

678
00:36:13.171 --> 00:36:15.561
Okay. Come on.
Let's go.

679
00:36:15.695 --> 00:36:27.485
♪

680
00:36:44.114 --> 00:36:45.594
People used to spend
the night in here?

681
00:36:47.205 --> 00:36:48.765
What are you doing?
Sara!

682
00:36:48.902 --> 00:36:50.822
-Sorry. Tabitha.
-[Tabitha] Open up!

683
00:36:50.947 --> 00:36:52.647
I'm sorry.
I'm doing this for you.

684
00:36:52.775 --> 00:36:54.035
I'm doing this
for all of us.

685
00:36:54.168 --> 00:36:56.738
Why are you sorry?
Just open the door. please!

686
00:36:56.866 --> 00:36:58.776
-I'm sorry.
-[Tabitha] Sara!

687
00:36:58.912 --> 00:37:01.962
Sara! Sara!

688
00:37:05.875 --> 00:37:07.655
Go get your sister.

689
00:37:10.010 --> 00:37:11.530
Father Khatri!

690
00:37:15.015 --> 00:37:18.495
Hey. I've got kind of
a weird question for you.

691
00:37:18.627 --> 00:37:21.757
If. uh...

692
00:37:21.891 --> 00:37:26.071
If someone asked for a sign.

693
00:37:26.200 --> 00:37:29.030
how would they know
what they were looking for?

694
00:37:33.251 --> 00:37:34.601
Sara?

695
00:37:34.730 --> 00:37:35.990
Looking for your sister?

696
00:37:36.123 --> 00:37:37.173
Yeah.

697
00:37:37.298 --> 00:37:38.948
She's not here.

698
00:37:39.082 --> 00:37:40.822
I saw her heading
towards the barn

699
00:37:40.954 --> 00:37:41.914
with that Matthews lady
and her boy.

700
00:37:44.000 --> 00:37:47.180
[Goats bleating]

701
00:37:47.308 --> 00:37:50.488
[Goats bleating]

702
00:37:55.751 --> 00:38:00.501
[Goats bleating]

703
00:38:03.933 --> 00:38:05.813
Where's my mom?

704
00:38:05.935 --> 00:38:07.935
She'll be right out.

705
00:38:09.069 --> 00:38:10.509
Come here.

706
00:38:12.159 --> 00:38:13.599
I need to tell you something.

707
00:38:14.727 --> 00:38:16.027
Sara!

708
00:38:16.163 --> 00:38:19.123
Ethan! Sara!

709
00:38:19.253 --> 00:38:21.693
I really like you.

710
00:38:21.821 --> 00:38:24.001
And what's about to happen.

711
00:38:24.127 --> 00:38:27.307
it's gonna save everyone.

712
00:38:27.435 --> 00:38:30.995
just like in one
of your stories.

713
00:38:31.134 --> 00:38:32.964
You're gonna be the hero.

714
00:38:35.356 --> 00:38:36.526
Where's my Mom?
I want my Mom!

715
00:38:36.662 --> 00:38:39.972
-We're doing this for her!
-[Nathan] Sara!

716
00:38:40.100 --> 00:38:41.930
-Sara. what are you doing?
-This is how we go home.

717
00:38:42.058 --> 00:38:43.228
Let him go.

718
00:38:43.364 --> 00:38:45.154
They told me.
this was the last one.

719
00:38:45.279 --> 00:38:46.759
then everyone gets to go home!

720
00:38:46.889 --> 00:38:49.019
Ethan! Sara!

721
00:38:50.893 --> 00:38:52.723
-[Grunts]
-[Nathan] Ethan. run!

722
00:38:52.852 --> 00:38:55.122
[Screams]
No! Let me go!

723
00:38:55.245 --> 00:38:57.595
You don't understand!

724
00:38:59.337 --> 00:39:02.037
Oh. my God. Ethan! Ethan!

725
00:39:02.165 --> 00:39:03.815
-[Gasps]
-[Sara] Nathan?

726
00:39:05.212 --> 00:39:07.082
Nathan?

727
00:39:07.214 --> 00:39:08.874
Nathan!

728
00:39:08.998 --> 00:39:09.908
[Gasps]

729
00:39:10.043 --> 00:39:12.133
No!

730
00:39:12.262 --> 00:39:13.792
No. Nathan!

731
00:39:13.916 --> 00:39:15.606
-Nathan.
-[Sara] Nathan. please!

732
00:39:15.744 --> 00:39:17.144
Nathan!

733
00:39:17.267 --> 00:39:18.917
Nathan! Nathan!

734
00:39:20.923 --> 00:39:21.843
Nathan! No!

735
00:39:21.968 --> 00:39:24.708
My God. please!

736
00:39:24.840 --> 00:39:26.580
Please. Nath...

737
00:39:34.502 --> 00:39:37.072
You guys are right.
It's not all bad here.

738
00:39:37.200 --> 00:39:39.860
[Giggles]

739
00:39:39.986 --> 00:39:42.076
You know. I was thinking.
when we get back to the house--

740
00:39:42.205 --> 00:39:43.245
-[Ethan] Julie!
-What?

741
00:39:43.381 --> 00:39:44.731
[Sobbing]

742
00:39:44.860 --> 00:39:46.170
Hey. Ethan?

743
00:39:46.296 --> 00:39:47.386
-[Ellis] Hey.
-[Ethan] Julie!

744
00:39:47.515 --> 00:39:49.125
Hey. hey. hey.
What's wrong?

745
00:39:49.256 --> 00:39:50.776
-Where's Mom and Dad?
-[Crying]

746
00:39:50.910 --> 00:39:52.220
Hey. what's wrong?

747
00:39:52.346 --> 00:39:53.696
It's okay. Don't cry.

748
00:39:53.826 --> 00:39:56.916
Come here. Come here.
Come here. It's okay. Shh.

749
00:39:57.046 --> 00:39:57.736
[Voices screaming]

750
00:39:57.873 --> 00:40:00.273
Oh. my God! Oh. my God!

751
00:40:00.398 --> 00:40:01.658
Oh. my God! Ethan!

752
00:40:01.790 --> 00:40:03.010
Tabitha!

753
00:40:03.139 --> 00:40:04.099
Ethan!

754
00:40:05.272 --> 00:40:06.972
[Banging]
[Tabitha] Help me!

755
00:40:07.100 --> 00:40:09.280
Please help me!

756
00:40:09.407 --> 00:40:10.837
Help me out here. please!

757
00:40:10.973 --> 00:40:12.153
[Jim] Tabitha!

758
00:40:12.279 --> 00:40:13.239
Tabitha!

759
00:40:13.367 --> 00:40:15.147
Jim! Jim. over here!

760
00:40:15.282 --> 00:40:17.112
You okay?

761
00:40:17.240 --> 00:40:18.290
Where-- where's Ethan?

762
00:40:18.416 --> 00:40:19.716
-What?
-Where's Ethan?!

763
00:40:19.852 --> 00:40:21.722
Go and find him!

764
00:40:21.854 --> 00:40:22.904
[Indistinct chatter]

765
00:40:23.029 --> 00:40:25.639
[Jim]
Ethan! Ethan!

766
00:40:25.771 --> 00:40:26.991
Jim!

767
00:40:27.120 --> 00:40:28.340
-[Julie] Mom!
-Jim. where's Ethan!?

768
00:40:28.469 --> 00:40:29.859
-[Julie] Dad!
-I don't know.

769
00:40:29.992 --> 00:40:31.082
-Where's Ethan?
-[Julie] Mom!

770
00:40:31.211 --> 00:40:33.211
Oh. my God! Ethan.

771
00:40:33.343 --> 00:40:34.783
-Oh. my God!
-[Ellis] Here you go.

772
00:40:34.910 --> 00:40:35.870
Oh. my God!

773
00:40:37.391 --> 00:40:38.961
Come here. come here.

774
00:40:39.088 --> 00:40:40.788
[Gasps]

775
00:40:40.916 --> 00:40:51.226
♪

776
00:40:58.934 --> 00:41:02.764
[Breathing heavily]

777
00:41:12.557 --> 00:41:13.857
-I was too late.
-Hold on.

778
00:41:13.993 --> 00:41:15.083
-I'm sorry.
-Hey.

779
00:41:15.211 --> 00:41:16.691
Jim. Tabitha.

780
00:41:18.171 --> 00:41:20.261
[Sighing]

781
00:41:20.390 --> 00:41:21.780
-How is he?
-He's fine. He's fine.

782
00:41:21.914 --> 00:41:24.094
-We're gonna go home.
-[Jim] You go on ahead. okay?

783
00:41:24.220 --> 00:41:25.870
-Come on. Jules.
-I'll catch up.

784
00:41:29.269 --> 00:41:31.489
Where is she?

785
00:41:31.619 --> 00:41:34.139
Uh. she. uh...
She ran off into the woods.

786
00:41:35.231 --> 00:41:37.501
And?

787
00:41:37.625 --> 00:41:40.885
And if she comes back before
dark. then we'll handle it.

788
00:41:41.020 --> 00:41:44.070
And if she doesn't?

789
00:41:44.197 --> 00:41:46.197
If she doesn't.
then it's handled.

790
00:41:49.463 --> 00:41:51.163
She came into my house.

791
00:41:52.161 --> 00:41:54.081
She played with my kid.

792
00:41:54.207 --> 00:41:56.117
I know.

793
00:41:56.252 --> 00:41:58.122
Look. if there's
anything that we can do--

794
00:41:58.254 --> 00:42:00.004
The fuck is
wrong with you people?

795
00:42:00.126 --> 00:42:02.476
You talk like this place
is fucking Mayberry!

796
00:42:02.607 --> 00:42:05.217
One big family.
is that what you said?

797
00:42:05.348 --> 00:42:07.048
Are you fucking kidding me?

798
00:42:10.179 --> 00:42:22.279
♪

799
00:42:29.503 --> 00:42:31.203
Where did you find him?

800
00:42:31.331 --> 00:42:35.991
Um. we were
just coming back...

801
00:42:36.118 --> 00:42:38.028
Well. it doesn't
really matter.

802
00:42:38.164 --> 00:42:40.344
But he was running up the hill
towards the Colony House.

803
00:42:40.470 --> 00:42:42.340
You did good. Julie.

804
00:42:50.480 --> 00:42:52.350
Can you take him upstairs
for a minute?

805
00:42:52.482 --> 00:42:54.012
'Kay.

806
00:42:54.136 --> 00:42:55.786
